{
  "texts": [
    "UP has the capability to train complex pooling functions and outperforms previous pooling methods in terms of performance.",
    "However, it should be noted that UP entails a significant computational cost.",
    "Williams et al.",
    "17 proposed a novel approach called Wavelet Pooling, which introduces wavelet pooling as an alternative to traditional neighborhood pooling in the field of convolutional neural networks.",
    "This method involves decomposing the input features into a second-level decomposition and discarding the first-level subbands to reduce the feature dimensionality."
  ]
}